<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have a few mildy funny stories.<P>Last night I was bored and headed down to good old CT.  There wasn't any groups in the throne room/tae temple so I thought I'd let superpet (49) go to town.  I was keeping the spawns in the TR clean and a twinked rogue showed up and started talking to me (actually setting me up for the "can you go kill such and such and give me his RS plz").  Anyways I put on see invis, and of course I'm not paying attention and the diviner spawns and charms me (sitting in illusion and having your illusion dispelled is amusing btw).  I kill my pet in one DM (?!).  Unfortunetly, see invis doesn't seem to count while you are charmed, or maybe its not possible for you to "aggro" players.  Anyways after charm broke and I killed the diviner I was given the "one pet at a time" message while trying to make a new one, and it wouldn't go away until I camped.<P>Another time I was camping the scryer in guk.  This time he charmed my pet, then me, then made his own pet.  When charm broke and I mezzed the pets and killed him, my old pet was completely stranded - non kos to me, but non responsive to mem blur.  However he assisted the frogluks (?!) and I had to kill him.<P>This next one is one of my favorite memories from EQ.  For some reason I had walked to qeynos around level 36.  As I entered qhills I thought, wth, I'll go check Hadden.  To my abject shock he was up, but I saw someone in a robe running near him.  He was blue to me and I unloaded with anarchy.  Unfortunetly his enchanter friend next to him didn't take kindly to that.  So I started running off, firing anarchy, and running, while being nuked by the enchanter.  So I get the kill on hadden, and I'm now less than a bubble of life left.  I hear the enchanter begin to cast a spell and I'm thinking, '#$%&* I didn't even get to loot, and of course I'm bound in freeport'... and he charms me.  It was then I remembered that charm memblurs, and charm breaks, the enchanter friend ignores me,  I rune myself and go loot the FBE.
</FONT>
