<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Had an interesting expierience with charm myself today. I was playing my iksar monk (level 19 at the time) and left the warrens to travel to Highpass, and decided to go the hard way and go the boat route. So I make it to Queynos, and I don't know where the dockside entrance to the sewers is, and I'm swimming around, an NPC near me casts a spell and I don't really notice and all of a sudden I'm CHARMED. I watch in dread as I go over to the stairs, walk past about 20 guards, and stand next to the enchantress (who cons yellow to me) on the dock (who has a pet of her own up already). I'm so sure that as soon as charm wears off I'm toast, so I Feign Death (which works while I'm charmed somehow). So i'm lying there praying, and all of a sudden she turns and attacks someone else, I never really see why, but I and her other pet chase down this level 1 human wizard and I kill him (still lying on the ground FD too). I have no idea what he must have thought of it, I never bothered to send him a tell and he didn't say anything about it. I was pretty amused by it tho, considering the situation.. anyway I follow her back to her spot on the dock, eventually charm wears off (I swear it felt like 5 minutes.. probably wasnt that long but at least 2 mins.) and immediately I re-feign death, as I wasn't sure if the other one worked as I was charmed, but I was not attacked by either her or the guards I walked by earlier, much to my relief. Eventually I get up the courage and I leap to my feet and run off, luckily she doesnt notice me in time to attack.
</FONT>
