Back when the AI was such that the only spell you'd cast was in slot 8, I got charmed both in the Gorge and in CT (throne room), and had to sit there helplessly while the game steered me into players.  I didn't have a useful spell in slot 8 or a weapon equipped, so that's all I did was steer into them.  Mind you it's a good idea to take the opposing enchanter out of the action, but I didn't make a very useful pet otherwise.  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>The other day I was in Skyshrine with my monk main (non-KOS to dragons) when I see a huge train go rushing past, with a PC at the head of it.  During the train, I see that something tries to attack me from behind, and as I instinctively Feign Death, I think "wow, someone trained up something from near Yelinak?" since that's on a different faction.  A PC nearby kills this being, and I hit F9 to see what's up.  I think, "an aggro gnome NPC?"  Then I do a /who all on the name and see that it's a player - the AI on charmed PCs doesn't account for faction, so I got attacked.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=3547" TARGET=_blank>Lini Coeurbrise</A><BR>49th level DE enchanter<BR>Bertoxxulous
