Speaking of charmed PCs and Paw - I was in a 4-person group there a while back, and two other people wanted to join us (one was a necro, forget who the other was).  We were doing well as-is but it's hard to find a pickup group in there and we felt kind of bad for them, so we invited them.  Well, they weren't the most experienced we found out, and one example was how they dealt with a charmed party member.  I'd put Resist Magic on the puller, a monk, but he got charmed on one pull.  The necro sic'd his pet on the *monk* and not on the enchanter gnoll, and the other pickup member attacked him as well.  As I was casting Entrance I spammed for them to back off him and get the gnoll.  Fortunately they listened before the mez hit, and I successfully mezzed the monk so he wouldn't be a bother, then chain-stunned the gnoll so he couldn't cast.  By the time mez broke, the charm had as well.<P>Oh, and I definitely have to bring Fippy into Qeynos finally - he so badly wants to go to town as you can tell from his shouts.  Think I'll charm him and take pictures of him in various spots if I can keep him as a pet that long - a friend of mine has an ingrained "kill all gnolls" reaction and would just flip out at seeing Fippy inside Qeynos.  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=3547" TARGET=_blank>Lini Coeurbrise</A><BR>49th level DE enchanter<BR>Bertoxxulous
