<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Couple things I have noticed about charm. <P>From duels with both Mages and Necros I have found that when you charm them, it only takes one hit from them to kill their former pet. <P>If you attack something that is green or really light blue a charmed PC/NPC will go in and melee it (even if it is a caster), while if you attack a blue or above they will cast spells if possible. <P>If you and a buddy caster are hunting, duel and charm them. A charmed PC switches to the NPC ruleset when charmed (Cast while running, almost impossible to interupt, spells cost about 1/4th as much) and charmed PC melee seem to hit harder and faster (no hard facts on this though).<P>When able, try to charm enemy clerics/shamans. Sit to med and they will heal and buff you  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> <P>The same thing applies to PvP. Was the druid quad kiting you for a bit before you landed a mez? Charm him and he will cure you and give you SoW, how nice.<P>--------------------<P>Taldra Yi`Tsarin<BR>Enchanter to Thowl Al'Shar<BR>Povar Server
</FONT>
