<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
About the most fun I ever had with Charm (aside from playing with guildies in PvP) was in NK one time when I was just goofing off.<P>Charmed a silvermist wolf and buffed him up real good and sicced him on a bear.  Even with all my buffs up on it, the wolf was still getting mauled and I thought he would die when along came....another wolf.  He automatically jumped in and assisted my pet.  After a few seconds the 2 wolves together brought the bear pretty low on HP and it started to run.  Bolted right past ANOTHER wolf, who also jumped in and assisted mine.<P>After they killed the bear I pulled a bug with Tash and let it hit me and my pet jumped in, and the others automatically joined it.  By the time the bug ate what was left of my poor puppy, another wolf had joined in as well!<P>The really cool part was that the wolves kept fighting the bug after my pet died.  He eventually ate them all, but it was really neat to see all those wolves come to the aid of my pet.  :-)<P>This could be kinda' fun for RP or Newbie-scaring value.  Run around with your own personal pack of wolves....  :-)<P>Teynor<BR>42nd Enchanter<BR>The Sentinent
</FONT>
